    <title>Marvel is releasing a manga starring a cat — oh yeah, and a Deadpool one</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="" src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/91GBnRolEWxa1_XEemJKVbiDVOs=/300x0:3540x2160/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/69170368/marvel_meow.0.png" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Marvel Meow&lt;em&gt;, starring Chewie.&lt;/em&gt; | Image: Marvel and Viz Media&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="XMi8UH"&gt;Marvel and manga publisher Viz Media &lt;a href="https://www.viz.com/news/newsroom/v/1006722"&gt;announced three Marvel-themed manga&lt;/a&gt; that will be released in English, and one of them features an adorable cat. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="Ga7Zrw"&gt;The first manga will be &lt;em&gt;Marvel Meow&lt;/em&gt;, starring Captain Marvel’s cat, Chewie. (If you follow Marvel’s Instagram account, you may have seen &lt;a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/BurJLGVlh8-/"&gt;some comics&lt;/a&gt; starring the furry feline already.) Based on Viz Media’s description, it sounds like her primary goal is to annoy people in the Marvel Cinematic Universe, which I approve.&lt;/p&gt;
